{
  "stem": "15577.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you have to know, we were living in such a-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] not knowing what will happen that there were even people who could work or who had to work, so-called a very good place to work, and they stopped working because they-- their-- they developed a kind of philosophy it's better not to work, not to be involved, not to be mixed with the German, but to stay what is called now ghetto B.",
      "word_count": 78
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then I can hide myself or so on and so on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Even such cases were there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were divided in these two ghettos, and then came a day-- in the meantime, we knew they are beginning to build a camp not far from Crakow, outside in Crakow.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's very close to Crakow.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now it belongs to Crakow, this place.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was the place where the Jewish cemetery was before.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they took out the stones and began to build [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the camp, which is Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "How did you know about it?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "First of all, it was a very close.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Secondly, as I told you, many of us were going out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So you could hear from both.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You could contact.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So there was one day when the ghetto was closed hermetically, and the Germans were selecting-- selecting people to go out but not to go out to work, because during a normal akcia, they allowed, let's say, our group to go out to work.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then the others stayed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This, who was allowed, went out to Plaszow-- was sent to the camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the-- and the other were left.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Who was left was the whole ghetto B and a part of ghetto A.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And all these were killed afterwards.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
